Patch Set 6:

There are some commanlities between legacy_parse_uri and https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/store/swift.py#L165 function. Is there any way there can be placed in a glance/common ?

Patch Set 6:

@Iccha, I think maybe we want some duplication in this case. My concern would be that the function changes or goes away and that would affect the migration, but that may be paranoia since ideally migration testing would notice something like that. We just don't want the behavior of a migration to change. Venkat what are your thoughts?

Patch Set 6:

Ok makes sense to keep them separate. Point taken

Patch Set 6: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

I am good with this the way it is venkat. Thanks for the patch.

Patch Set 6: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

(1 inline comment)

Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I don't think we should import from one migration script to another. Especially not when we're altering history (i.e. changing a migration that has already been released.)

Patch Set 6:

Thanks Mark for pointing me that its not good idea to import one migration script to another. 

Even though the main focus of this patch was to refactor the code to make all the BadStoreUri exceptions thrown from 'legacy_parse_uri' logged along with its respective image_id's, I found the 'legacy_parse_uri' function being duplicated and hence included the removal of duplication too (for which I had to import one migration script into another) as part of this patch set.

Need your suggestion if I can submit another patch set for review that includes only changes for logging image_id along with BadStoreURI(without including the removal of duplication of 'legacy_parse_uri' function changes).

Thank you Mark, Alex, Iccha and Arnaud for reviewing this patch and leaving your valuable comments.
